---
---

<section id="learning" class="section-wrap">

  <div class="reveal">
    <div class="section-eyebrow">
      <span class="section-num">10 / Currently pursuing</span>
    </div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Never done<br/>learning.</h2>
  </div>

  <p class="reveal" data-delay="0.05s" style="font-size: 1.05rem; color: var(--fg); margin-bottom: 48px; max-width: 600px; line-height: 1.8;">
    Full-time engineer by day, full-time student by night.
    The overlap between cloud, infrastructure, and security is where I want to go deep.
  </p>

  <div class="learning-grid reveal" data-delay="0.1s">

    <!-- Masters -->
    <div class="learning-card learning-card--active">
      <div class="learning-card__header">
        <div>
          <div class="font-mono" style="font-size: 0.72rem; letter-spacing: 0.12em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--amber); margin-bottom: 8px;">
            In progress
          </div>
          <h3 style="font-family: 'Syne', sans-serif; font-weight: 700; font-size: 1.35rem; color: var(--fg); letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin-bottom: 4px;">
            MSc Cybersecurity &amp; Privacy
          </h3>
          <div class="font-mono" style="font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--fg-2);">
            Universitat Oberta de Catalunya (UOC)
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="learning-status">
          <span class="status-dot-amber"></span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p style="font-size: 0.95rem; color: var(--fg-2); line-height: 1.8; margin-top: 16px;">
        A rigorous programme focused on security audit, compliance frameworks, and privacy engineering —
        studied entirely alongside full-time work. Currently in the thesis phase, researching
        how to assess and improve a company's alignment with <span style="color: var(--fg);">ISO 27001</span> and
        <span style="color: var(--fg);">SOC 2</span> — bridging the gap between technical controls
        and formal audit capability.
      </p>

      <div style="display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 6px; margin-top: 16px;">
        {['Security audit', 'ISO 27001', 'SOC 2', 'Compliance', 'Privacy engineering', 'Risk assessment'].map(t => (
          <span class="ptag">{t}</span>
        ))}
      </div>

      <!-- Thesis callout -->
      <div style="margin-top: 16px; padding: 16px 20px; border-left: 2px solid var(--amber); background: rgba(232,162,48,0.04);">
        <div class="font-mono" style="font-size: 0.72rem; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--amber); margin-bottom: 4px;">Master's thesis</div>
        <p style="font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--fg); line-height: 1.7;">
          Evaluating and improving ISO &amp; SOC 2 compliance capability within a real organisation —
          from gap analysis to control implementation.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Certs on radar -->
    <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 12px;">

      <div class="font-mono" style="font-size: 0.72rem; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--fg-2); margin-bottom: 8px;">
        On the radar
      </div>

      <div class="learning-card learning-card--radar">
        <div style="display: flex; align-items: flex-start; justify-content: space-between; gap: 16px;">
          <div>
            <div style="font-family: 'Syne', sans-serif; font-weight: 700; font-size: 1.05rem; color: var(--fg); margin-bottom: 4px;">
              CKA — Certified Kubernetes Administrator
            </div>
            <div class="font-mono" style="font-size: 0.72rem; color: var(--fg-2);">CNCF / Linux Foundation</div>
          </div>
          <span class="ptag" style="flex-shrink: 0;">K8s</span>
        </div>
        <p style="font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--fg-2); line-height: 1.7; margin-top: 12px;">
          Running Kubernetes in the homelab daily — the CKA would formalise what's already hands-on practice.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="learning-card learning-card--radar">
        <div style="display: flex; align-items: flex-start; justify-content: space-between; gap: 16px;">
          <div>
            <div style="font-family: 'Syne', sans-serif; font-weight: 700; font-size: 1.05rem; color: var(--fg); margin-bottom: 4px;">
              GCP Professional Cloud Architect
            </div>
            <div class="font-mono" style="font-size: 0.72rem; color: var(--fg-2);">Google Cloud</div>
          </div>
          <span class="ptag" style="flex-shrink: 0;">GCP</span>
        </div>
        <p style="font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--fg-2); line-height: 1.7; margin-top: 12px;">
          AWS is covered. GCP would complete the multi-cloud picture and open new architecture conversations.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Current mindset -->
      <div style="padding: 20px 24px; border: 1px solid var(--border); margin-top: 4px;">
        <div class="font-mono" style="font-size: 0.72rem; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--fg-2); margin-bottom: 8px;">Current mindset</div>
        <p style="font-size: 0.95rem; color: var(--fg); line-height: 1.7; font-style: italic;">
          "Not sure which to tackle next — but I'll be tackling one of them."
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>

</section>

<style>
  .learning-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 24px;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .learning-card {
    padding: 24px;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    background: var(--bg-2);
  }

  .learning-card--active {
    border-color: rgba(232, 162, 48, 0.2);
    background: rgba(232, 162, 48, 0.03);
  }

  .learning-card--radar {
    padding: 18px 20px;
    background: var(--bg);
  }

  .learning-card__header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 16px;
  }

  .learning-status {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    padding-top: 4px;
  }

  .status-dot-amber {
    display: block;
    width: 8px;
    height: 8px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--amber);
    animation: amberPulse 2.5s ease-in-out infinite;
  }

  @keyframes amberPulse {
    0%, 100% { opacity: 1; box-shadow: 0 0 0 0 rgba(232, 162, 48, 0.4); }
    50%       { opacity: 0.8; box-shadow: 0 0 0 6px rgba(232, 162, 48, 0); }
  }

  @media (max-width: 860px) {
    .learning-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 32px;
    }
  }
</style>
